\section{Cubic regularization}{

These parameters control the adaptive cubic model
\eqn{m_k(s) = f_k + g_k^\top s + \tfrac{1}{2} s^\top H_k s +
\tfrac{\sigma_k}{3} \|s\|^3} and the sigma adaptation rule (Algorithm
2a/2b of \code{design/pseudocode.qmd}).
\describe{
\item{\code{sigma0}}{Initial regularization parameter (default \code{1.0}).}
\item{\code{sigma_min}}{Floor on \code{sigma_k} (default \code{1e-6}). Prevents the
cubic term from vanishing entirely on flat regions.}
\item{\code{sigma_max}}{Ceiling on \code{sigma_k} (default \code{1e12}). Triggers
emergency-stop behavior when reached.}
\item{\code{eta1}}{Step-acceptance threshold; steps with \eqn{\rho_k \ge
    \texttt{eta1}} are accepted (default \code{0.1}).}
\item{\code{eta2}}{Very-successful threshold; \eqn{\rho_k \ge
    \texttt{eta2}} triggers \code{sigma} shrinkage (default \code{0.9}).}
\item{\code{gamma1}}{Multiplicative shrink factor on a very-successful
step (default \code{0.5}).}
\item{\code{gamma2}}{Multiplicative grow factor on an unsuccessful step
(default \code{2.0}).}
}
}

\section{Trust-region fallback (cubic to TR on flat-ridge detection)}{

Cubic regularization can stagnate in "flat-ridge" regimes — iterations
with the regularization floor pinned, model predictions matching the
objective (\eqn{\rho \approx 1}), gradient stalling, and a Hessian
that is positive-definite but nearly singular. This is outside the
local-error-bound condition of Yue, Zhou & So (2018) under which
cubic regularization is guaranteed to converge quadratically at
degenerate minimizers. arcopt detects the regime and switches once
from the cubic subproblem to a trust-region subproblem.
\describe{
\item{\code{tr_fallback_enabled}}{One-way cubic to TR switch
(default \code{TRUE}).}
\item{\code{tr_fallback_window}}{Sliding-window length for the detector
(default \code{10}).}
\item{\code{tr_fallback_tol_ridge}}{\code{lambda_min(H)} threshold defining a
"near-singular PD" Hessian (default \code{1e-3}).}
\item{\code{tr_fallback_rho_tol}}{Tolerance on \verb{|rho - 1|} for the
"near-perfect model" signal (default \code{0.1}).}
\item{\code{tr_fallback_grad_decrease_max}}{Ratio of latest to oldest
\verb{||g||_inf} above which the gradient counts as stagnant
(default \code{0.9}).}
\item{\code{tr_fallback_g_inf_floor}}{Absolute lower bound on \verb{||g||_inf}
below which the switch will not fire — keeps the hybrid from
triggering at true local minima (default \code{1e-6}).}
\item{\code{tr_r0}}{Initial trust-region radius at the switch
(default \code{1.0}).}
\item{\code{tr_rmax}}{Maximum trust-region radius (default \code{100}).}
\item{\code{tr_eta1}}{TR step-acceptance threshold (default \code{0.25}).}
\item{\code{tr_eta2}}{TR expansion threshold (default \code{0.75}).}
\item{\code{tr_gamma_shrink}}{Radius shrink factor on a poor step
(default \code{0.25}).}
\item{\code{tr_gamma_grow}}{Radius grow factor on a very-good
boundary step (default \code{2.0}).}
}
