\section{Quasi-Newton polish (cubic to BFGS line-search)}{

Once the iterate enters the quadratic attraction basin of a strict
local minimum, the cubic regularization penalty has decayed to its
floor and contributes negligible damping, but arcopt still evaluates
\code{hess()} every iteration. For expensive Hessians (analytic AD via
Stan, finite differences) this dominates wall-clock time. Polish
mode replaces the cubic subproblem with a Wolfe line search along the
BFGS-approximated Newton direction, skipping further \code{hess()} calls
until convergence or until the BFGS approximation drifts.

Off by default in v0.2.0 because the existing manuscript and benchmark
problems converge before the five-signal healthy-basin detector
accumulates a full window. Enable opt-in for long-running smooth
problems with expensive Hessians.
\describe{
\item{\code{qn_polish_enabled}}{Enable the cubic to qn_polish bidirectional
switch (default \code{FALSE}).}
\item{\code{qn_polish_window}}{Sliding-window length for the healthy-
basin detector (default \code{5}).}
\item{\code{qn_polish_rho}}{Minimum \code{rho_k} required throughout the
window (default \code{0.9}).}
\item{\code{qn_polish_lambda_min}}{Minimum \code{lambda_min(H_k)} required
throughout the window (default \code{1e-3}).}
\item{\code{qn_polish_g_decay}}{Maximum ratio of consecutive \verb{||g||_inf}
values; e.g. \code{0.5} requires 2x-per-iteration contraction
(default \code{0.5}).}
\item{\code{qn_polish_g_inf_floor}}{Absolute lower bound on \verb{||g||_inf}
at window start; prevents firing at convergence (default \code{1e-8}).}
\item{\code{qn_polish_c1}, \code{qn_polish_c2}}{Wolfe line-search constants
(defaults \code{1e-4} and \code{0.9}).}
\item{\code{qn_polish_alpha_max}}{Initial step length tried by the line
search (default \code{1.0}).}
\item{\code{qn_polish_max_ls_iter}}{Maximum line-search evaluations per
iteration (default \code{20}).}
\item{\code{qn_polish_max_fail}}{Consecutive line-search failures that
trigger a revert to cubic mode (default \code{3}).}
\item{\code{qn_polish_reenter_delay}}{Cubic iterations required after a
revert before qn_polish may re-fire (default \code{5}).}
\item{\code{qn_polish_curv_eps}}{Curvature threshold for skipping BFGS
updates to preserve PD (default \code{1e-10}).}
}
